del powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"89cb7f40-8aac-d58c-f76e-e490d8c2645b","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Custom Logic Tool\n\nDeterministic code helper the agent can invoke for exact computation.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1510],"id":"4b8a4615-980f-3674-a476-ab4de37da5f5","name":"Note: Custom Logic Tool"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Run Calculations\n\nMath tool — keeps arithmetic exact instead of letting the LLM guess.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[790,1750],"id":"4479f5f3-b8f0-be2d-516d-f96044033b75","name":"Note: Run Calculations"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Search Reference Wiki\n\nReference lookup tool for general-knowledge questions.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1249,1510],"id":"df1ba95c-d465-9b23-dd74-a5320494b920","name":"Note: Search Reference Wiki"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Conversation Memory\n\nConversation memory keyed by session — the bot remembers earlier turns for each user separately.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `memory`\n\n🔑 Postgres connection","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1006,1090],"id":"a38d4d18-1b46-e6a6-6b5f-7363b17f6fe4","name":"Note: Conversation Memory"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Shape Agent Output\n\nShapes the item: writes `answer`, `confidence`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Confident Enough?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1573,520],"id":"30069f75-6797-4eff-ff1d-d93d82b81033","name":"Note: Shape Agent Output"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Confident Enough?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.confidence }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Deliver Answer + Log to Notion · ②→ Escalate to Human Queue","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1897,520],"id":"c90aca14-4d77-ef0d-3904-5ddd86215139","name":"Note: Confident Enough?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Deliver Answer + Log to Notion\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2221,280],"id":"b4005a97-a97c-3dee-6922-29d4cab59c02","name":"Note: Deliver Answer + Log to Notion"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate to Human Queue\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2545,880],"id":"d392ef17-7807-4fce-e030-6b4a17c762e1","name":"Note: Escalate to Human Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Join Outcomes\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3193,520],"id":"88d86b6f-aa2d-2373-677a-5a27ed4c84eb","name":"Note: Join Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4165,520],"id":"631f9117-68fa-0fcb-c082-e6a159adfa9d","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4489,520],"id":"e0e62e15-6e85-a109-c68d-49fe5ea3b8c4","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4813,520],"id":"43e6e481-07a3-276e-68d8-6464508397f4","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5137,520],"id":"9127a3c5-e04c-09ca-f84f-b4c22202dd74","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per conversation (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5461,520],"id":"f7ce7d7b-f5ed-e365-77dc-a6cbdbbb2982","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5785,520],"id":"6668b7b3-e7ab-7e12-ecca-4b0a97489887","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6109,520],"id":"7134ed42-f18b-a59f-5653-161c1c27571e","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6433,520],"id":"0eb756b6-9757-40db-d271-1f458606b78b","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6757,520],"id":"e29899e4-9c15-df07-3548-efff1e2e1458","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Stamp Completion Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7081,520],"id":"3488ec96-2760-867a-364d-5fe809f04bad","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7405,520],"id":"3cf9705f-e63a-9783-f324-bf49f56971dd","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7729,520],"id":"fcb4b78f-1fa0-1df6-bb30-aa95543935f7","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8053,520],"id":"0eb52df9-add8-3bde-0757-789c206290f5","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8377,520],"id":"292b9cec-155e-4c11-9277-e03d0e87dca4","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8701,520],"id":"f2a7775f-f3cd-82ed-dcab-8464c5c31157","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8053,1540],"id":"4ae7eb6e-68ee-7d0b-9f83-34a30ba31f34","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8377,1540],"id":"9c67ff60-014d-4949-7280-93a2cef4d152","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8701,1540],"id":"668c9b2e-75f5-21e6-2dff-fb8d4f469e11","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Handle chat messages for Voice (07694)\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nHandle chat messages for Voice (07694). It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual voice is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Normalize Conversation Payload → Reason & Act (AI Agent) → Shape Agent Output → Confident Enough? → Deliver Answer + Log to Notion → Join Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating voice in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; OpenAI API key; Postgres connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"af4ce1c9-d19f-fc05-05df-37b9d21cb4cf","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"a524bd2d-f3b1-1e75-23d1-242e6d35c9b9","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"2cf637c3-363d-971a-0544-bb2dffb36c6c","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"60ef6097-1be9-f628-eec5-d5efad2e7385","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your voice process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"f14f43b0-a231-3263-389b-da23d082b1b8","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Normalize Conversation Payload","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Normalize Conversation Payload":{"main":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Custom Logic Tool":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Run Calculations":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Search Reference Wiki":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Conversation Memory":{"ai_memory":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_memory","index":0}]]},"Reason & Act (AI Agent)":{"main":[[{"node":"Shape Agent Output","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Shape Agent Output":{"main":[[{"node":"Confident Enough?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Confident Enough?":{"main":[[{"node":"Deliver Answer + Log to Notion","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Escalate to Human Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Deliver Answer + Log to Notion":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate to Human Queue":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Join Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"45dda1d1-df54-415e-a247-4e6f08b36038","id":"FDX07694"}